Class Map

java.lang.Object
Map
public class Map
extends java.lang.Object
This class contains the map information, including the map name, gold required to win, and the map structure.

    • readMetaData

      private java.lang.String readMetaData​(java.lang.String line, java.lang.String metaDataTitle) throws MapException
      Takes in a line and the meta data string and checks whether the line contains information of that meta data, if so, it returns the meta data
      Parameters:
      line - String read from file
      metaDataTitle - String that the line should start with
      Returns:
      String representing the line after removing the metadata title
      Throws:
      MapException - If the line is null, the metadata title is missing or if there is no value after the title.

    • readMap

      private java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> readMap​(java.util.Scanner scnr) throws MapException
      Attempts to read the map, returning it if successful, otherwise throwing a MapException error with description as to what went wrong
      Parameters:
      scnr - Scanner reading in the file
      Returns:
      ArrayList of strings which stores each row of the map as a string.
      Throws:
      MapException - If there is an in invalid character in the map or if there is not enough spaces for the players and bots.

    • validateMap

      protected void validateMap​(java.io.File f) throws MapException
      Validates whether a given file contains a valid map or not, if not then it throws a MapException with the reasoning as to why not.
      Parameters:
      f - file to read map from
      Throws:
      MapException - If any cases from from readMetaData and readMap, if file is not found or the win argument does not contain a valid integer
